.TH diodmount 8 "@META_DATE@" "@META_ALIAS@" "@META_NAME@"
.SH NAME
diodmount \- mount diod file systems
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B diodmount
.I "[OPTIONS]"
.I HOST:/dir
.I dir
.LP
.B diodmount
.I "--list-exports HOST"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B diodmount
is the mount utility for the distributed I/O daemon.
.LP
This command must be run as root.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I "-x, --list-exports HOST"
List file systems exported by HOST.
.TP
.I "-u, --mount-user USER"
Causes the file system to be mounted so that only USER can access it.
.TP
.I "-p, --private-server"
Spawn a server dedicated to I/O forwarding for USER.
This option can only be used in conjunction with \fI--mount-user\fR.
.TP
.I "-n, --no-mtab"
Do not update /etc/mtab.  This may be appropriate, for example, when
the file system is mounted in a private name space.
.TP
.I "-c, --diodctl-port PORT"
Connect to the diodctl server on a port other than its default (10005).
.TP
.I "-d, --diod-port PORT"
Connect to the diod server on a port other than its default (10006).
This option does not work with \fI--private-server\fR
as a port will be dynamically assigned to the private server.
.TP
.I "-o, --diod-options OPT,[OPT,...]"
Pass additional 9P mount options when mounting the 
.B diod
server.
Do not specify the \fIport\fR, \fIuname\fR, \fIaname\fR, \fImsize\fR,
or \fIaccess\fR options as 
.B diodmount
already sets the value of these options.
.TP
.I "-O, --diodctl-options OPT,[OPT,...]"
Pass additional 9P mount when mouting the
.B diodctl
server.
Do not specify the \fIport\fR, \fIuname\fR, \fIaname\fR, or \fIaccess\fR
options as 
.B diodmount
already sets the value of these options.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.LP
List the file systems exported by tycho42:
.nf
    diodmount -x tycho42
.fi
.LP
Mount /g/g99 from tycho42, so that all users can access it:
.nf
    diodmount tycho42:/g/g99 /g/g99
.fi
.LP
Mount tycho42's diodctl server directly for testing:
.nf
    diodmount tycho42:/diodctl /g/g99
.fi
.LP
Mount /p/lcrater1 on tycho[101-164], with a private server for garlick:
.nf
    pdsh -w tycho[101-164] \\
        diodmount -p -u garlick tycho42:/p/lcrater1 /p/lcrater1
.fi
.nf
.SH "SEE ALSO"
diod (8),
diodctl (8),
diod.conf (5)
